-
The mundsburg towers were built in the early 1970s and are about 100 meters in height. Two of the towers house 1 and 2 room apartments, one tower houses office space. At the base of the towers is the Mundsburg Center located, which houses a cinema, plenty of restaurants, grocery stores and other shopping opportunities. The towers are one of the very few tries to establish inner-city high-rise construction in the premium segment in Hamburg, but it never managed to gain widespread popularity. I wanted to give a somewhat new perspective of the towers and tried out some light trail photography/editing in the process. Hope you like it!
